          </div>

          <p class="text-[17px] leading-relaxed text-gray-800 mb-4">The hidden cost of DIY is your time and your risk. A back injury on moving day costs you weeks of work. A scratched bannister costs hundreds to repair. A dropped TV costs the price of a new one. None of these are covered when you do it yourself.</p>

          <p class="text-[17px] leading-relaxed text-gray-800 mb-8">A popular middle ground is to pack your own boxes over two weeks, then hire professionals to load the van, drive, and unload. You save money on the packing labour while still getting the expertise and insurance for the heavy, risky part of the move.</p>
